llm_column_description: The `district_id` column in the `district` table serves as the primary key, uniquely identifying each district.
The A2 column in the district table primarily stores the name of the district.
The A3 column in the district table primarily represents the name of the city or region within the district.
The A4 column in the district table primarily represents the population of the district.
The A5 column in the district table represents a specific attribute of the district, stored as a TEXT value.
The A6 column in the district table represents a specific attribute of the district, stored as text.
The A7 column in the district table represents a specific attribute of the district, likely a categorical or numerical value related to the district's characteristics.
The A8 column in the district table primarily represents a numerical attribute related to the district, likely serving as a quantitative measure or identifier.
The A9 column in the district table represents an integer value that is not null.
The A10 column in the district table represents a real number value that is not null.
The A11 column in the district table represents the average salary in the district.
The A12 column in the district table represents a real number that is nullable.
The A13 column in the district table represents a real number value that is not null.
The A14 column in the district table represents an integer value that is not null, indicating a required numerical attribute specific to each district.
The A15 column in the district table stores an integer value that is nullable.
The A16 column in the district table represents an integer value that is not null, serving as a required numerical attribute for each district.
